gmails vs mutt:
  gmails wins for replying: sets In-Reply-To/References headers automatically
  via the API, so threading works correctly. Use gmails reply/fwd for conversations.
  mutt wins for fire-and-send one-liners: direct SMTP is faster than Python
  startup + OAuth + REST API. Use mutt (or the `send` alias) for quick sends.
  For reading/listing/searching, always use gmails.
"""


